    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.54-55_0001" />
                
                <note type="curatorial">211 Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">54</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    62 <hi rend="caps">NORTH FRANKLIN STREET
                        <lb/>
                    WILKES-BARRE
                        <lb/>
                    PENNSYLVANIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 21st 1920</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you for your cordial letter. I tried to find a copy of the two poems you wrote of, in our City Library &#8212; before I had your kind offer &#8212; but only found "Prayer for Pain" and "Envoi" in a book called The New Poetry. An Anthology.</p>
                
                <p>I would be most glad to have either, "Song of Hugh Glass" or "Song of Three Friends," whichever you can best spare me a copy of&#8212;
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.54-55_0002a"/>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">55</fw>
                
                    I would have sent you an answer sooner but have been under orders to remain at home and in bed a week. When I was young I felt old, now that I am getting to be so, I go ahead as if I was a team of young horses.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>With many thanks, I am</salute>
                    <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                
                    <signed>Natalie S.B. Forsyth</signed>
                
                    <signed>Mrs. G.A.F.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.7.54-55_0002b"/>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    W<unclear cert="high">ILKES</unclear>-BARRE
                    APR 21
                    11 30PM
                    1920
                    PA.
                </ab>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>2 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S.POSTAG<unclear reason="missing" cert="high">E</unclear> 2 CENTS <unclear reason="missing" cert="high">2</unclear></p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bancroft</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Nebraska</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
            </div1>
